verbose_text: As equal ChGnTI and AtGnTI mRNA steady state levels resulted in equal protein steady state levels, we therefore assume that HuGnTI mRNA is as efficiently translated in plants as AtGnTI mRNA and the reduced activity of HuGnTI is therefore ascribed to post-translational characteristics such as the apparent reduced protein stability, mis targetting or reduced activity of the catalytic domain of HuGnTI.
